<ce:para>In the presence of fluctuating electricity prices, the smart grid provides optimization opportunities for power-intensive processes. We present an MILP model that integrates operational and strategic decision-making for power-intensive processes. Strategic decisions involve installing additional equipment, upgrading existing equipment, or increasing storage capacity that potentially facilitate cost savings at the operational level. We provide a case study for an air separation plant based on industrial data, which demonstrates the impact of investments in terms of annual cost savings. Â© 2012 Elsevier B.V.</ce:para>
